// The sync guarantee: `x11_only` exists only in the x11 variant. Under the wayland backend the call
// is unresolved, and the COMPILER and the ANALYZER must agree — the editor can't green-light a call
// the build rejects. Under x11 both must be clean.
//
// Compiler: rejects under wayland, accepts under x11.
// RUN: not env ARCHE_SELECT=vgfx=wayland %arche check %s
// RUN: env ARCHE_SELECT=vgfx=x11 %arche check %s
//
// Analyzer: reports the SAME error under wayland, and is clean under x11.
// RUN: env ARCHE_SELECT=vgfx=wayland %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | grep "has no member 'x11_only'"
// RUN: env ARCHE_SELECT=vgfx=x11 %analyzer --dump %s 2>&1 | not grep "has no member"
#import { vgfx }
main :: proc() {
  vgfx.x11_only();
}
